Section 1:
1 L.D. 1303
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 533, L.D. 1303, “An Act to Amend the
10 Laws Governing Qualifications for the State Auditor”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §242, as amended by PL 2015, c. 44, §4, is further amended to
13 read:
14 §242. Organization; deputy
15 The Office of the State Auditor must be organized in the manner the State Auditor
16 considers best suited to the accomplishment of its functions. The office may have those
17 auditors, assistants and employees as the State Auditor may require, but they are subject to
18 the Civil Service Law.
19 Any person elected to the position of State Auditor or any person permanently
20 employed by the Office of the State Auditor as deputy auditor, director of audits or assistant
21 director of audits must be currently qualified as or have successfully completed or passed
22 the examination for a certified public accountant, certified information systems auditor or
23 certified internal auditor. Persons not so qualified may be employed in these audit
24 supervisory positions on a temporary basis not to exceed 9 months.
25 In the event of a vacancy in the office of State Auditor because of death, resignation,
26 removal or other cause, the deputy auditor shall perform the duties of the office until a State
27 Auditor has been appointed in conformity with section 241 and has been duly qualified. In
28 the event of absence or disability of the State Auditor, the deputy auditor shall likewise
29 perform the duties of the office during the State Auditor's absence.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment amends the bill by retaining the provisions in current law governing
3344 the qualifications of any person permanently employed by the Office of the State Auditor
Page 1 - 132LR1492(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 533, L.D. 1303
315 as deputy auditor, director of audits or assistant director of audits as well as the provisions
326 governing the duties of the deputy auditor in the event of a vacancy in the office of State
337 Auditor because of death, resignation, removal or other cause.
Page 2 - 132LR1492(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
